# Tests templates (from `tests.json`)

Summarizes **710** files matching **`*.test.ts`**, **`*.test.tsx`**, **`*.spec.ts`** (see [`.agents/file-lists/tests.json`](../file-lists/tests.json)). Framework: **Vitest**; UI: **`@testing-library/react`**, **`fireEvent`** (not `userEvent`) per **`@testing-standards.mdc`**.

## Inventory snapshot

| Fact | Typical value |
| --- | --- |
| Extensions | `.ts` / `.tsx` roughly even; small `.js` |
| Path depth (median) | 6 segments |
| Common roots | `app/pages` (~45%), `app/utils` (~21%), `app/features` (~15%), `app/components` (~10%) |
| Largest slice | `app/pages/Result/...` (~41%) |

**Co-location:** `Foo.test.tsx` next to `Foo.tsx`; `utility.test.ts` next to `utility.ts`.

## Template — component snapshot

```typescript
import { render } from "@testing-library/react";
import { createSnapshotRootElm } from "test-utils/createSnapshotRootElm";
import { describe, expect, it } from "vitest";

import Foo from "./Foo";

describe("Foo", () => {
  it("renders correctly", (): void => {
    render(<Foo />);
    expect(createSnapshotRootElm()).toMatchSnapshot();
  });
});
```

## Template — utility

```typescript
import { describe, expect, it } from "vitest";

import { addOne } from "./addOne";

describe("addOne", () => {
  it("adds one", () => {
    expect(addOne(1)).toBe(2);
  });
});
```

## Policy pointers

- **Do not mock** internal components/stores for UI snapshots unless **`rules-bundle-react.mdc`** exceptions apply.
- **100% coverage** target for utilities: **`@utility-test-coverage-standards.mdc`**.

